SIMPLE: nullity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nullity
<hw>Nul"li*ty</hw> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧l"l⟦icr⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Nullities</plw>.</plu> <ety>[LL.
<ets>nullitias</ets>, fr. L. <ets>nullus</ets> none: cf. F.
<ets>nullit⟦eacute⟧</ets> . See <er>Null</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being null; nothingness;
want of efficacy or force.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Nonexistence; <as>as, a decree of
<ex>nullity</ex> of marriage is a decree that no legal marriage
exists</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which is null.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Was it not absurd to say that the convention was supreme in the
state, and yet a <qex>nullity</qex>?</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Numb</ent>⟦br⟧
